        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): show WebChat the restart recovery notice via the session transcript",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #87808.\n\nWhen the Gateway restarts mid-turn during a WebChat direct chat (bundled Codex harness), the interrupted turn is marked unresumable and the user is supposed to receive a recovery notice. But that notice is delivered via `message.action` (an outbound channel send), and WebChat is an internal-only channel that rejects `message.action`. So `resolveRestartRecoveryDeliveryContext` returns `undefined` (WebChat fails `isDeliverableMessageChannel`), the notice is silently dropped, and on reconnect the turn just vanishes — no assistant reply, no interruption notice. The user has to send another message to discover what happened.\n\n## What changed\n\n**`src/agents/main-session-restart-recovery.ts`** — in `sendUnresumableSessionNotice`, detect the WebChat (internal) channel from the raw delivery channel *before* the deliverable-channel filter. For WebChat, persist the recovery notice to the session transcript via `appendInjectedAssistantMessageToTranscript` (a gateway-injected assistant message written to disk + a live transcript update) instead of an outbound `message.action`, so a reconnecting WebChat client renders the terminal notice. Non-WebChat channels keep the existing `message.action` delivery.\n\n**`src/agents/main-session-restart-recovery.test.ts`** — regression test: an unresumable WebChat session no longer issues an outbound `message.action`, and the recovery notice is persisted to the transcript (read back from disk).\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** An interrupted WebChat turn now leaves a visible terminal notice in the session transcript instead of silently vanishing on reconnect. The notice is persisted to disk so a reconnecting WebChat client renders it; non-WebChat channels keep their outbound delivery.\n\n**Real environment tested:** Local worktree of `origin/main` at base `118060157d`, Node v22.22.0. Drove the real `recoverRestartAbortedMainSessions` → `sendUnresumableSessionNotice` path via `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs`, against a real on-disk session store + transcript (`sessions.json` + `main-session.jsonl`). The notice is read back from the real transcript file.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n```\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/agents/main-session-restart-recovery.test.ts -t \"WebChat transcript\"\n# Baseline measured by git-stashing the recovery fix and re-running the same test.\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix:** With the fix stashed (origin behavior), the WebChat session's transcript never gets the notice and the test fails:\n```\nsrc/agents/main-session-restart-recovery.test.ts (21 tests | 1 failed | 20 skipped)\nAssertionError: expected '{\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",...}}' to contain \"couldn't safely resume\"\n```\nWith the fix applied, the notice is persisted and the full suite passes:\n```\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\n     Tests  21 passed (21)\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** The unresumable WebChat session no longer issues an outbound `message.action` (WebChat would reject it); instead the recovery notice (\"…couldn't safely resume…\") is written to the session transcript on disk, where a reconnecting WebChat client reads it. Session status is still marked `failed`.\n\n**Live end-to-end proof (real Gateway restart + real model turn + reconnect):** `scripts/repro/webchat-restart-recovery-notice-live-proof.mts` spawns a real isolated Gateway instance backed by a real `zte/step3p5-flash` model, sends a real WebChat `chat.send` turn, then **SIGKILLs the Gateway mid-turn** — a graceful SIGTERM would release the transcript lock, so only a hard crash leaves the stale lock restart-recovery keys on. Restarting over the same state dir runs startup restart-recovery, whose own gateway logs show the causal chain:\n```\n[gateway] removed stale session lock: <sessionId>.jsonl.lock (dead-pid)\n[main-session-restart-recovery] marked 1 interrupted main session(s) from stale transcript locks\n[main-session-restart-recovery] persisted interrupted main session recovery notice to transcript: agent:main:main (transcript tail is not resumable)\n[main-session-restart-recovery] main-session restart recovery complete: recovered=0 failed=1 skipped=0\n```\nOn reconnect, `chat.history` (the WebChat reconnect read-path) returns the recovery notice as the assistant message, with the session now `status: failed` / `abortedLastRun: true` / `deliveryContext.channel: webchat`:\n```\n{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I was interrupted by a gateway restart and couldn't safely resume the previous turn. Please send that last request again and I'll pick it up cleanly.\"}]}\n```\nReproduced 3×, all green. Run: `OPENCLAW_TEST_FAST=1 node --import tsx scripts/repro/webchat-restart-recovery-notice-live-proof.mts`\n\n**What was not tested:** No rendered browser/Control-UI screenshot — the reconnect is verified through the `chat.history` API (the exact read-path the WebChat client uses), not a UI capture.\n\n## Validation (supplemental)\n\n- `main-session-restart-recovery.test.ts` full suite → 21 passed (before fix: WebChat case fails as shown above)\n- `tsgo:core:test` → no new errors in changed files; `oxlint` → clean\n",
